The POSP series is world famous for its quality and is current military issue for the Red Army. It is built battlefield-tough from magnesium alloy and has fully multi-coated optics. Specifications:

Aimpoint CompM4 sights are the finest sights that Aimpoint has ever produced. The improved energy efficiency provides up to 8 years of continuous use from a single AA battery! Aimpoint CompM4 sights incorporate an integral mount that eliminates the need for a separate ring and can be customized with vertical and forward spacers to fit a variety of firearms. They can also be used by hunters and sport shooters that need night vision compatibility. CompM4 sights are available in two versions. The two versions are identical except that the CompM4 offers a high battery compartment, while the CompM4S offers a low battery compartment. The Aimpoint CompM4 is now the latest version of the US Army's M68 CCO (Close-Combat Optic), continuing a legacy that Aimpoint has maintained since 1997. The performance of the CompM4 sights is optimized for use with all generations of Night Vision Devices (NVDs), but is especially suited for 3rd generation night vision technology. Aimpoint's unique band-pass coating on the front lens reflects select frequencies of red light at near 100% efficiency in order to give the highest possible dot brightness with the smallest amount of energy while transmitting nearly 100% of light in the Infrared and near-infrared part of the spectrum to provide the clearest, brightest image possible when used with a 3rd generation NVD. With 7 NVD-compatible brightness settings and 9 Daylight settings including one extra-bright setting, the CompM4 and CompM4S are ready for use around the clock.

title: For Sale:  vz24 8mm Mauser
location: St. Tammany Parish, New Orleans, Louisiana
postcontent:
This is a 1940 vz24. Based on the famous M48 patterned rifle, the vz24 was built in Czechoslovakia under German occupation during WWII. This particular rifle was built at the Brno factory in 1940 and issued to Romanian forces fighting for the Axis Powers. Records show that this rifle and many more like it were put to use along the Eastern Front during the war.

The rifle is relatively clean and shoots exceptionally well for its age. Obvious signs of use but nothing catastrophic or even significant, just character. Action functions smoothly and I've had zero malfunctions in firing over 200 rounds with it. 

Rifle comes with about 150-200 (I'm too lazy to count it) rounds of 8mm surplus ammo in an ammo can. Some are on stripper clips and others are in boxes and from various manufacturers. 

A great gun for the history buff, hunter, or your every day Sergeant Schultz!

You must be 18 years old and a Louisiana resident to purchase. You must sign a bill of sale with diver's license number. No exceptions.

No trades. Price is firm. This is non-negotiable so please don't waste your time trying.

title: For Sale:  1995 AM General Hummer
postcontent:
This is a 1995 AM General Hummer 4 hard door Open Top. It is not a H1. In order for it to be a H1 then the H2 would have had to have been in existence, which it was not. Let's face it, ISIS got some, the Russians stole some, the Chinese copied it, and this is cheaper than a fiberglass wannabe Gorilla kit. And it is the absolute most American piece of hardware short of an Apache helicopter.

This badassery is powered by a marine block 350 ci 5.7 gasoline engine/4L80-E trans with 153k miles. (Which AM General made for two years when gas was cheap).The exterior is painted with krylon flat tan, so scratches are a 30 second fix. This vehicle has power windows, power locks, power mirrors, Central Tire Inflation System, (not currently connected), and sits on modified H2 17" wheels with 38x13.50 directional tires. Comes with owner's manual and PDF of parts list.

I had this vehicle for 5 years and have invested approximately $40k in restoration. I have receipts from work done. Ninety percent of the work was done by Benzin Motors in Tulsa or by myself. To include: New Hood, Hood Snubbers, CTIS repair, Air pump with female connection for power tools, Ugraded HVAC (entirely), Ball joints, lower control arms, Water pump, pitman arms, Entropy Machining Neoprene seat covers, Reupholstered interior, New top and bed cover, New battery, Complete coolant system flush, AM/FM with external connection, Rhino bumper mounted spare tire carrier, brush guard, windshield light bar, heavy duty rear bumper, military turn signals, new headlights, brakes, exhaust, 2" body lift, main brake line, rebuilt transfer case, and receiver hitch for towing jeeps (kidding, former jeep owner here). Much more, much more. 

The vehicle comes with a lot of extra parts to include: another set of seats, 1 extra spare H2 wheel, set of 4 1-piece 16.5" steel wheels, set of 4 16.5" two-piece wheels, front skid plate, CTIS wheel connections, and other small pieces.

Issues, need to clean rust on passenger frame rail, and seepage on right rear brake caliper.

To alleviate any questions, I do not know the miles per gallon. I measure it in fun per mile. If you ask, this likely is not the vehicle for you. It is not bullet proof (see Open Top), it does not float, it does not have a turbo diesel, it is not a military surplus truck bought for $300 (I know, your uncle's cousin's friend bought 20 of them), it will not withstand an IED blast, and it is not a kit. Furthermore, it is not a Zombie apocalypse vehicle (See Open Top), because Zombies do not exist, and there is no warranty.

This vehicle is not for you if your tool kit is from sharper image, you mind people staring (H2 owners won't even look at you), or mind people asking you questions, (I am literally pumping gas into it and some dude asks me if it is a diesel), you cannot stand the taste of beer, you like to drive and accelerate fast, or you have yet to part with your My Little Pony collection.

This vehicle is for you if you can turn a wrench (righty tighty-lefty loosy), you dream of smashing a smart car, own a gun or two, you have money to buy it, enjoy prius driver sneers, you want to own an exceptional piece of Americana, you understand the love-hate relationship with vehicles, and you enjoy pulling up next to jacked up trucks and your tires are still bigger. 

The price $27,560. 85. I am negotiable with the $0.85. NADA prices it between $14k and $42k. No tire kickers please. Have money, have a plan, contact me to buy the vehicle I have wanted since I was a kid. No trades but would consider leasing for movies if it's starring Kiera Knightly.
